In his weekly address, President Trump highlighted the signing of the NASA Transition Authorization Act, which reaffirms the nation's commitment to NASA's mission of exploration and discovery. He discussed the Hubble Space Telescope and its significant discoveries, particularly the Hubble Deep Field, which showed thousands of galaxies in a seemingly empty region of the night sky. The President also mentioned the upcoming launch of the James Webb Space Telescope, which will further explore the universe's earliest stars and galaxies. He emphasized the importance of viewing old questions with fresh eyes and having the courage to seek answers in new places. The President expressed confidence in America's problem-solving abilities and stated that there is no challenge too great for the nation to overcome.